  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Verifying Compile Success**\n\nThe compilation of `index.html` was extremely fast. I\'ve confirmed a clean build, with no dependency issues, using `tsc --noEmit` and `vite build`. The speed and lack of errors suggest our static content is ready. Now I\'ll proceed with the next steps outlined in the instructions.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have designed and built the **Culling Games (Jogo do Abate) - Central Control Panel** as a fully interactive, responsive, military-grade single-page dashboard. \n\nThe application has been created as a **single, plain HTML5 file** styled exclusively with **Tailwind CSS** (via CDN) and containing robust vanilla JavaScript for state management, satisfying your requirements completely.\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual Identity & Design System\n* **Atmospheric Tactical Interface:** The design employs a dark mode theme matching the ominous, high-stakes vibe of Jujutsu Kaisen. It features a deep base (`bg-zinc-950`), card elements in `bg-zinc-900`, a live-ticking UTC system clock, and subtle scanline effects that mimic military monitors.\n* **Cursed Energy Accent System:** Action points utilize **Deep Purple** (`text-purple-400`, `bg-purple-700`), life indicators use **Spectral Green** (`text-emerald-400`), and death/danger notifications use **Crimson Red** (`text-red-500`).\n* **High Contrast Typography:** Headers and stats leverage uppercase styles with generous letter spacing using the **Space Grotesk** display font, paired with **Inter** for descriptions and **JetBrains Mono** for points and logs.\n\n---\n\n### \360\237\225\271\357\270\217 High-Fidelity Interactive Capabilities\nThe interface is fully functional, dynamic, and state-retaining using `localStorage`:\n\n1. **The Registration Zone (Participation Form):**\n   * Allows registering new sorcerers with fields for **Name**, **Starting Colony**, **Cursed Technique**, **Starting Points**, and initial **Life Status**.\n   * Styled with custom dark inputs, subtle borders, and a deep violet/crimson gradient button to enter the games.\n   \n2. **Point Transfer Mechanism (Rule #10):**\n   * A secondary tab in the left-side zone allows you to select any two active players and transfer points between them.\n   * Real-time checks ensure a sender has sufficient points before executing the transaction under the rules of the game board.\n\n3. **Active Monitoring Grid & Player Cards:**\n   * Features preloaded seed profiles for major combatants like **Yuta Okkotsu**, **Hajime Kashimo**, **Hiromi Higuruma**, and **Megumi Fushiguro**.\n   * Displays the sorcerer\'s name, colony, cursed technique description, and points in high-contrast numbers.\n   * Includes interactive triggers for **Adding/Subtracting Points** (+1/-1), **Quick Eradication** (Delete), and **Life Status Toggling** (switching between Alive and Deceased). Deceased players are visually greyed out with an elegant strike-through name.\n\n4. **Advanced Query Filters:**\n   * Contains a live search input to filter sorcerers by name or technique.\n   * Colony dropdown filters allow inspecting specific active battlefields.\n   * Status tabs isolate **All**, **Alive**, or **Deceased** participants instantly.\n\n5. **Kogane Broadcast Feed & Rules Manual:**\n   * A terminal log in the lower-left corner outputs instant game events (e.g., entrance announcements, deaths, point alterations).\n   * A custom rules modal references Kenjaku\'s binding rules (Rule 1, 2, 5, 10, and 11) for full lore immersion."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 1
      nanos: 448897804
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
