he Starting Points input, and the Initial Status select, applying the Immersive UI design consistently. My goal is pixel-perfect alignment.\n\n\n**Styling Registration Buttons**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the submit button\'s design in the registration form, replacing existing styling with a new class structure. I\'ve updated the button with a red background, white text, and shadow effects. I\'m also now updating the Point Transfer simulator with new labels and new input selects to align with the \"Immersive UI\".\n\n\n**Updating Point Transfer UI**\n\nI\'m now implementing the point transfer section. I\'ve styled the receiver label, select, amount label, input, and transfer button. I\'m focusing on ensuring consistency with the \"Immersive UI\" design. The goal is to make the transfer section intuitive and visually appealing, using a mix of colors and effects.\n\n\n**Analyzing Statistics Panel**\n\nI\'m now diving into the right-side statistics bar, starting with the registered users section. I\'m focusing on its structure and styling, specifically the grid layout and class attributes, aiming to enhance the visual appeal within the Immersive UI design, translating it into tailwind directives. I\'m currently working to improve consistency.\n\n\n\n**Designing Monitoring Header**\n\nI\'m now starting on the monitoring header, building a grid for stats like active sorcerers and total points. I\'m focusing on text styling: small, uppercase labels and large, bold values. I\'m using `text-zinc-500` and `text-zinc-100` for consistent color. I\'m aiming for a sleek, visually impactful layout.\n\n\n**Refining Statistic Values**\n\nI\'m now refining the statistics display within the monitoring header, specifically the values themselves. I\'m focusing on the \"Deceased Rate\" which needs styling. I\'m using `text-2xl md:text-3xl` for size and `font-black` for emphasis, along with color updates. The goal is a visually clear and impactful presentation.\n\n\\n\\nI\'m now working on 