isplay for Cursed Techniques. Now, the player cards will show either the declared technique, or a placeholder if none is specified. I\'m focusing on the visual presentation, using a subtle italic style for the placeholder. I have also used the `font-sans` class so it will integrate well. Now, I\'m integrating the controls for point adjustments on the UI.\n\n\n\n**Adding Point Controls**\n\nI\'ve integrated the point adjustment controls for each player card. These controls dynamically enable or disable based on player status, ensuring only alive players can have their points modified. The controls now render as part of the player card and interact with the logic. I am also integrating a delete button for player management.\n\n\n**Adding Delete Button**\n\nI\'ve added the delete button to each player card, integrating the final piece of the design. The button\'s style mirrors the existing design, ensuring a consistent visual experience. I\'ve double-checked the classes and styles for the card wrapper; all features match the existing styling.\n\n\n"
